pohue
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a name used for several native climbing plants: a) convolvulus; b) clematis; c) a Muehlenbeckia. [Maori pohutukawa[o-macron]] <i>Calystegia sepium</i>, bell climber, bindweed, greater convolvulus
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
